# Calorie Estimation Engine

This is the **most critical** subsystem. Full spec: `PRD.md` → "Calorie Estimation Engine".

## API (`POST /api/estimate`)

- Model: `claude-sonnet-4-6`
- Tool: `web_search_20260209`, `max_uses: 3`, **unrestricted web** (no `allowed_domains`); prompt steers toward authoritative sources (`WEB_SEARCH_PREFERRED_DOMAINS`)
- **Response shape:** `{ meals: MealEstimate[] }` — the model may split one input (e.g. `טוסט ושוקו`) into multiple independent meals, each with its own `text_he` + breakdown
- **Zod** validate before return; retry parse **once** (no tools); then error → client manual entry
- Log (don't reject) per meal if `sum(breakdown.calories) !== calories` (±1 kcal)

## Cache flow (client or shared lib)

1. Normalize: trim, collapse whitespace, lowercase
2. `getDoc(estimationCache/{normalized})` — if &lt;30 days → `AI_CACHED` (stored as `meals[]`; legacy flat docs wrapped into one meal)
3. Else call API → write cache → `AI`
4. Client (`day-view`) applies `estimates[0]` to the pending row; on split, creates extra rows in the same slot via `createMealFromEstimate`

## Persisted breakdown edits

- Store `originalCalories`, `originalPortionGrams` on each row for linear scaling
- `portionGrams === null` → direct calorie edit UI
- Recompute meal `calories` = sum(breakdown); set `caloriesSource: MANUAL_BREAKDOWN_EDIT`

## Cost

- One-shot messages only (no history)
- Never call Claude from the browser
